Description: Sherd of wall of Aeolian pottery dinos; interior glazed; exterior: part of duck to right followed by goat (horn and ear preserved); red on breast of bird. Graffito on exterior.
Producer name: Attributed to: The London Dinos Group
Curator's comments: Pencil '111' on inside. Probably from same vase as 1924,1201.1028 and 1965,0930.710; possibly from the same vase as Boston MFA 88.949.
Bibliographic references: Lemos 1991 / Archaic Pottery of Chios. The Decorated Styles (p. 252, no. 399)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.76)
